Key Match Events: Jamal Musiala scored once and set up three more goals as Germany crushed Hungary 5-0.
Niclas Füllkrug scored the first goal with a tap-in from Musiala's assist in the 27th minute.
Kai Havertz hit the crossbar with a header in the 33rd minute and fired narrowly wide in first half stoppage time.
Musiala scored Germany's second goal in the 58th minute on a quick counter-attack.
Florian Wirtz scored the third goal after a one-two with Musiala in the 66th minute.
Musiala assisted Aleksandar Pavlovic's goal in the 77th minute.
Kai Havertz scored a penalty in the 81st minute.
Post-Match Reflections: Scorer Niclas Füllkrug praised Jamal Musiala's form and the team's deep runs and control of the game.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match took place at Merkur Spiel-Arena in Düsseldorf, Germany with an attendance of 49,235.
